videos.description: Grayson Allen shows off his quickness by losing the defender with a spin move leaving the Duke guard wide open for the easy basket.
videos.headline: Grayson Allen's sweet spin move scores easy bucket

videos.description: Frank Jackson races through the lane and soars toward the basket, switching hands at the last moment for the tough layup.
videos.headline: Jackson soars and switches hands for layup

videos.description: Off the missed shot, Miami completely ignores boxing out Marques Bolden who flies in to throw down the massive putback dunk.
videos.headline: Bolden throws down huge putback dunk

videos.description: Going for a rebound, Grayson Allen gets inadvertently smacked across the face and heads to the bench to patch up some bleeding.
videos.headline: Grayson Allen accidentally gets smacked in the face

videos.description: Miami finishes off a 9-0 run when Kamari Murphy slams home the putback dunk to quite the crowd at Cameron Indoor Stadium.
videos.headline: Putback dunk caps off Miami's run

videos.description: Already with a cut on his head, Grayson Allen adds an injured finger to his rough first 20 minutes after going for a rebound and ending in excruciating pain.
videos.headline: Grayson Allen injures finger just before the half in win

videos.description: M. Jones made Three Point Jumper.
videos.headline: Duke gets the steal and hits the 3 pointer

videos.description: Duke intercepts the Miami possession, recovered the ball and finds Matt Jones who sinks a 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Duke grabs loose ball and Jones sinks 3

videos.description: Grayson Allen gets a piece of the ball and in transition Luke Kennard finds Harry Giles for the layup to put Duke up 54-40.
videos.headline: Allen deflects ball, Duke scores in transition

videos.description: Down 11 at the half, Duke utilizes a 20-0 run and outscores Miami 45-22 in the second half en route to a 70-58 victory.
videos.headline: Duke takes off in second half to down Miami
